#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:6
msgid "Accessibility Considerations"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:7
msgid "Consider attendees who may need accommodations for a disability"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:9
msgid "Mobility"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:11
msgid ""
"üçé Reserve seats in rooms for folks who might need it (wheelchair, "
"crutches, cane, etc.). Choose easily accessible seats, such as at the end"
" of a row on the aisle."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:12
msgid ""
"üçé Create wide aisles (2.5 m, so two power chairs can pass each other) "
"between chairs to make it easier for people who are mobility-impaired to "
"navigate the room."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:13
msgid ""
"Reduce conference sprawl to support access for people who are mobility-"
"impaired."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:14
msgid ""
"Consider marking and enforcing \"No Standing Zones\" through rooms such "
"as foyers that are both gathering areas and regions people must pass "
"through. (A 2.5 m \"corridor\" marked on the ground in yellow tape is "
"ideal.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:15
msgid ""
"Consider making remote access available via livestream, recorded talks, "
"etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:16
msgid ""
"Make sure the building is wheelchair accessible. (In the U.S. this is "
"typically required by law.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:17
msgid ""
"Be aware of how far/near the closest wheelchair-accessible restrooms are."
" Attempt to shorten this distance when possible, and be sure all staff "
"know where to direct attendees who require a wheelchair-accessible "
"restroom."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:19
msgid "Create Access Visual & Hearing Disabilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:21
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Book sign-language interpreters and/or real-time captioning (someone "
"typing captions) for deaf and hard-of-hearing attendees."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:22
msgid ""
"If the budget does not allow for both sign-language interpreters and "
"captioning, we suggest that you opt for captioning, as it tends to create"
" more access for a higher number of people. (See \"Further Reading\" "
"below.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:23
msgid ""
"Select a venue that has a hearing loop, or audio induction loop (a "
"special type of sound system for use by people with hearing aids) and "
"make sure it is used"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:25
msgid "Signage"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:26
msgid ""
"Consider using patterns rather than just color on signs and presentation "
"slides to indicate differences, to make comprehension easier for "
"attendees with color blindness/low vision issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:27
msgid "Provide large-text signs and easy-to-read maps."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:28
msgid "Send maps to attendees in advance, with the event schedule."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:29
msgid ""
"Provide large-print copies of printed materials, such as program "
"booklets, via printing normally A5 documents on A4, or folded A4-booklets"
" on A3."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:31
msgid "Microphones"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:32
msgid ""
"üçé Ask conference organizers to announce important information over the "
"microphone, which helps people with impaired vision."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:33
msgid "Make sure that hand-held microphones are available"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:34
msgid ""
"Encourage session chairs to repeat questions from the audience over the "
"mic so everyone can hear"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/04_venue_selection.md:35
msgid ""
"Session chairs should ensure that the microphone is used (even if the "
"speaker thinks their voice is loud enough)"
msgstr ""

